{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/85308", "id": 645021245, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NjQ1MDIxMjQ1", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/85308", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/85308.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/85308.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/85308", "number": 85308, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "[EXPERIMENT] Reduction of monomorphization load through type erasure", "user": {"login": "cjgillot", "id": 1822483, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE4MjI0ODM=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1822483?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/cjgillot", "html_url": "https://github.com/cjgillot", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cjgillot/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cjgillot/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cjgillot/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cjgillot/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cjgillot/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cjgillot/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cjgillot/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cjgillot/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cjgillot/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "This is an early proposition in response to #77960 through type-erasure of a function's MIR. This is still an experiment, and there are probably a lot of edge cases I did not cover. Any weird addition to the test cases is welcomed :smile:\r\n\r\nHere is the description I gave in https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/77960#issuecomment-821857686. Consider a function\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nfn foo<T>(a: M<T>) -> R<T> {\r\n  let c: C<T> = T::CONST;\r\n  // stuff with T\r\n  T::bar(a, c)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nDuring MIR analyses, the trampoline and the callee version can be computed generically:\r\n* gather all constants inside MIR body, and replace them by appropriately-typed parameters;\r\n* gather all functions, and replace them by function pointer parameters.\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nfn foo<T>(a: M<T>) -> R<T> {\r\n  let _2: C<T> = T::CONST;\r\n  let _3: fn(M<T>, C<T>) -> R<T> = T::bar;\r\n  foo_impl<T>(a, _2, _3)\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn foo_impl<T>(a: M<T>, c: C<T>, _3: fn(M<T>, C<T>) -> R<T>) -> R<T> {\r\n  // stuff with T\r\n  _3(a, c)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe next step is to only have one instance of foo_impl. In rustc parlance, I introduced an new variant `InstanceDef::ErasedShim` to encode it. It is resolved when some a MIR call terminator has the new flag `erased = true`. In order to define the substitutions for this instance, we replace all the type parameters by `u8`. The code becomes:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\ntype T_impl = u8; // We do not need it to satisfy any trait except Sized.\r\n\r\nfn foo<T>(a: M<T>) -> R<T> {\r\n  let _2: C<T> = T::CONST;\r\n  let _3: fn(M<T>, C<T>) -> R<T> = T::bar;\r\n  transmute(foo_impl(transmute(a), transmute(_2), transmute(_3)))\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn foo_impl(a: M<T_impl>, c: C<T_impl>, _3: fn(M<T_impl>, C<T_impl>) -> R<T_impl>) -> R<T_impl> {\r\n  // stuff with T_impl\r\n  _3(a, c)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nFor this transformation to be sound, we need to check that all those transmutes are safe.\r\n\r\nThe problem is that Rust layouts all monomorphized types independently: in general `M<T>` and `M<T_impl>` have no reason to have a similar layout if T != U. In special cases, this can happen, for instance if `M<T>` only points to sized T through a reference.\r\n\r\nAs a consequence, we need to check that `M<T>` and `M<T_impl>` and all recursively accessible types have the same layout. Likewise for `C<T>` and `R<T>`. If any such test fails, the type-erasure is unsound, we need to abort and go back to full monomorphization. Actually, we should be able to restrict the check to all types that are involved in the MIR: types of locals, of accessed fields, of dereferenced pointers...\r\n\r\nThe implementation actually does this in reverse. First, we check the layout in the function `gather_types`, and bail out if there is an incompatibility. Second, we gather and replace all the constants in the MIR. Handling drops requires to convert them into calls to `drop_in_place` in the same step. Third, we build the caller MIR. Finally, we erased all the type parameters in the callee MIR.\r\n\r\ncc @jumbatm @jyn514 ", "created_at": "2021-05-14T22:26:59Z", "updated_at": "2021-09-15T17:13:04Z", "closed_at": "2021-09-15T17:13:04Z", "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "b1683283c700ee38f8528fd6e4d4e65dd66a9ba9", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [{"id": 583436937, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw1ODM0MzY5Mzc=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/S-waiting-on-author", "name": "S-waiting-on-author", "color": "d3dddd", "default": false, "description": "Status: This is awaiting some action (such as code changes or more information) from the author."}], "milestone": null, "draft": true, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/85308/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/85308/comments", "review_comment_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/comments{/number}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/85308/comments", "statuses_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/statuses/25370adae6c361918aa2130d3d35c8e359b8c98b", "head": {"label": "cjgillot:dynamorph", "ref": "dynamorph", "sha": "25370adae6c361918aa2130d3d35c8e359b8c98b", "user": {"login": "cjgillot", "id": 1822483, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE4MjI0ODM=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1822483?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/cjgillot", "html_url": "https: